oy31/myhomepage/photo.html WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Best zone?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Howdy Paidin,<br>
<br>
For what you looking for the place to be is Boulder, Colorado.  Your within a 2hr drive of over a dozen major ski resorts.  Warren Miller's ski company is based there.  It's a college town with great sophistication so finding fine foods (and brews) shouldn't be a problem.  There are the 400ft vertical flatirons jutting up from the base of the rockies if you like climbing.  Lots of olympic athletes live and train there as do many extremists (people who've done everest, k2, etc.).  More miles of bike paths then miles of roads.  The 7-11 and Coors Light bicycle teams are based there and practice against each other daily on the roads and mts. Also the IFGS is based there if your ever interested in Live Roleplaying where you beat each other up with padded swords, maces, staves etc. while wearing medieval battle gear.  Lots of creative people there to.  Was in a group there in college that created BattleTech (mech warrior universe) and Ars Magica (great RP game).  <br>
<br>
I wouldn't suggest living here in Phoenix, AZ.  Too darn hot.  Town is growing too fast (2nd fastest in the nation).  No weather or earthquakes but very hot in the summer (110+ Farenheit).  Infrastructure can't keep up with the population growth.  The few pro's:  Bars on every block and drive thru liquer stores, Mexico is a 3hr drive away (4hrs to the ocean in Mexico), incredible scenery and huge vistas all within a two hour drive, best sunsets in the world (this is the west after all).<br>
<br>
